{
  "files": [
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "lib/request.js"
    },
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "test/req.host.js"
    },
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "History.md"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The deprecated req.host property was identified in three key files within the Express.js repository (sg-evals/expressjs-express):\n\n1. **lib/request.js** (lines 452-456): This file contains the actual definition of the deprecated req.host property. Line 452 includes a TODO comment noting \"change req.host to return host in next major\", and lines 454-456 define the property using deprecate.function() with the deprecation message 'req.host: Use req.hostname instead'. The property internally returns this.hostname, which is the correct non-deprecated replacement.\n\n2. **test/req.host.js**: This test file contains comprehensive test cases for the deprecated req.host property, with multiple test cases verifying its behavior including handling of hostnames, port stripping, IPv6 hosts, and trust proxy functionality. The file contains numerous references to req.host across multiple test cases (lines 12, 25, 39, 51, 64, 80, 96, 112, 128, 145).\n\n3. **History.md**: The changelog file contains multiple references to req.host documenting its history and deprecation:\n   - Line 2726: \"Added `req.host`\" (version 3.0.0beta2 - initial introduction)\n   - Line 1436: \"fix `req.host` for IPv6 literals\" (version 4.1.2)\n   - Line 799: \"Fix `req.host` when using \\\"trust proxy\\\" hops count\" (version 4.12.1)\n   - Line 1284: \"add `req.hostname` -- correct name for what `req.host` returns\" (version 4.3.0)\n   - Line 1286: \"deprecate `req.host` -- use `req.hostname` instead\" (version 4.3.0)\n\nThese files represent the complete set of source files that define, test, and document the deprecated req.host property, distinguishing it from the current req.hostname property that was introduced as its replacement in Express 4.3.0."
}

